gomodel:SYNGO_4815  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4,5: subcellular fractions from rat striatum showed that PDE10A is localized to postsynaptic fractions, associates with membrane fractions but not the PSD fraction (like e.g. NMDA1 and PSD95). Authors conclude; \"These results suggest that PDE10A associates with membranes through a non-ionic interaction.\"\n\nFigure 7: Localization of PDE10A in rat striatum by immuno-electron microscopy. Particles were observed at the edge of PSDs but not directly apposed to these structures (and not in presynaptic terminals at all).. Experimental description: Figure 7: \"Localization of PDE10A in rat striatum\"\n\nantibody:\nPDE10A mouse monoclonal antibody 24F3.F11 (1:1000)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4815" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

